etymology.description: semantic: 𤣩("jade") + phonetic: 黃(黃) (huáng, "yellow") = jade with similar sound to 黃 -> semicircular jade
etymology.interpretation: The character 璜 combines the jade radical 𤣩, indicating its material nature, with 黃(黃) (huáng, "yellow") as the phonetic component, indicating the pronunciation. This suggests a type of jade named for its yellowish hue or associated value.
